## Net-new modules (Phase 2 — scaffolded with test scaffolding, not bare stubs)

```
backend/
├── llm_gateway/   ← thin axum proxy (decision A), OpenAI-compatible upstream.
│                    Tier-aware refusal hooks (refs I.3 forbidden-components +
│                    compliance-tiers), prompt-audit span (IX.6), token budget +
│                    kill switch (XI.5), PII guard (XI.6), non-AI fallback (XI.5).
├── mcp/           ← rmcp server(s) via #[tool_router]. Dual transport behind
│                    Cargo features: transport/stdio.rs (default) +
│                    transport/http.rs (StreamableHttpService, auth → Zitadel).
│                    ≥1 stub tool among db | file | search.
└── rag/           ← pipeline: chunking + embeddings (Embedder trait:
                     MistralEmbedder default, LocalEmbedder fastembed fallback),
                     hybrid retrieval (vector + BM25 + RRF), coarse→exact
                     re-ranking, pgvector HNSW (vector_cosine_ops). Heavy work
                     runs as Temporal activity-only workers.
```

> The Rust module source + Cargo manifests + dependency pins (`rmcp`,
> `pgvector`, `async-openai`, `fastembed`) land in Phase 2. Pins live ONLY in
> the rendered `Cargo.toml.tmpl` (`ADR-B7-2-003`), never in the standards.

